# Community: Know Who You're Organizing With

A people management system built for organizers who need to understand relationships, not just store contact information. Track engagement, recognize patterns, and stay connected to the humans behind the data.

## Overview

Community organizing lives in the details: who attended which events, who's connected to whom, what matters to each person. Belcoda's community module treats these details as the foundation of effective organizing rather than administrative overhead.

The system adapts to how you already think about your community. Search by name, filter by participation patterns, group by affinity or geography. Tag people with the labels that make sense for your work. Every interaction—event signup, message exchange, group membership change—enriches the profile automatically, building context over time without manual data entry.

---

## Rich Profile Management

### Comprehensive Contact Information

Each person's profile captures everything you need to stay connected: email addresses, phone numbers, physical addresses, and preferred communication channels. But it also tracks verification status—whether someone's confirmed their email, verified their phone number, or connected via WhatsApp—so you know which channels are actually working.

Profiles include standard fields for organizational context: who they work for, their position, what groups they belong to, who their point of contact is within your organization. Social media links connect digital presence to real-world participation. Custom fields let you track whatever matters to your specific organizing context—skills, availability, interests, languages spoken beyond the primary preference.

The system respects consent clearly. Email and phone subscription status appear prominently, alongside a "do not contact" flag that's honored across all communications. You'll never accidentally message someone who's opted out.

### Edit in Place, Save Automatically

Profile editing feels lightweight. Click a pencil icon, change what needs changing, click save. Or cancel—nothing's permanent until you confirm. Forms validate as you type, catching errors before you submit. Field-level permissions ensure people can only edit what they should.

Profile pictures upload directly, with automatic optimization. Status fields let you add free-text context that makes sense for your work—"attending regional meeting," "interested in phone banking," whatever helps your team coordinate.

