## Activity Timeline

### See the Full Story

Every person's profile includes a complete activity timeline: messages sent and received, events attended, tags added and removed, group memberships changed. The timeline scrolls infinitely backward, loading twenty items at a time, newest first.

Each activity type renders distinctly. WhatsApp messages show the actual message content—text, images, audio, video—with delivery status (sent, delivered, read, failed). Email notifications appear with subject lines. Event signups link to the event details. Tag additions and removals name the tag and timestamp the change.

Activities aren't just logs—they're navigable. Click a tag name to view the tag. Click an event to see event details. Click a group to view membership. The timeline becomes a map of someone's engagement with your organizing work.

### Track Communication Across Channels

The timeline integrates email and WhatsApp equally. See when someone received an event reminder via email and when they replied via WhatsApp. See when automated messages were delivered and whether they were read. Emoji reactions appear inline, showing how people responded to messages.

For WhatsApp specifically, the system tracks message status granularly: pending, sent, delivered, read, failed. When messages fail, the timeline shows why. When they succeed, you see exactly when they were delivered and read.

