## Point Person System

### Distributed Management

Large communities need distributed responsibility. The point person system lets you assign a contact person to each community member—someone who's responsible for that relationship, who can make decisions about communications and engagement.

Point people unlock permission scoping. Group organizers can manage people they're point person for, even if they're not workspace administrators. This enables local leadership without requiring centralized approval for every action.

The system tracks point person assignments as part of the profile, visible to anyone viewing the person. Assignments can change as organizing relationships evolve. Default assignments can be configured during person creation, streamlining onboarding.

