## Import and Integration

### Bulk Creation

CSV import handles initial database population or regular synchronization with external systems. Upload a CSV, map columns to person fields, and let the queue processor handle the rest. The system tracks import progress: total rows, processed rows, failed rows. Failed entries include error details so you can correct and retry.

Imports are workspace-scoped and track who initiated them. Import history provides an audit trail of when and how records entered your database.

### External IDs

The external ID field supports integration with other platforms. Store IDs from your previous CRM, your event registration system, your donation platform. Use external IDs to match records during import or to synchronize updates bidirectionally.

