## Custom Fields

### Adapt to Your Context

Every organizing context is different. Some organizations need to track language skills, others dietary restrictions, others professional expertise. Rather than forcing a one-size-fits-all schema, Belcoda lets you define custom fields at the workspace level.

Create text fields for free-form input, number fields for quantities, date fields for important dates, boolean fields for yes/no attributes. Create select fields with predefined options, or multi-select fields when people need multiple choices. Label each field clearly, mark fields as optional or required.

Custom fields integrate fully with the rest of the system. They appear in profile forms, in list views (optionally), and in data exports. Filter by custom field values using the search system. The fields are flexible without being chaotic—workspace-level schema definition ensures consistency across your team.

