## Permissions and Access Control

### Granular Control

Not everyone needs to see everything. Belcoda's permission system supports multiple tiers:

**Owners** have unrestricted access—they created the workspace or were granted ownership rights.
**Admins** can manage most resources but can't change ownership or billing.
**Group admins** can manage people and communications within their assigned groups.
**Point persons** can manage people they're assigned as contact for.
**Regular users** can view information but not edit.

These permissions cascade logically. If you can edit a person, you can view their full profile. If you can manage a group, you can add or remove members. The system doesn't require manual permission assignment for every action—it infers appropriate access from roles and relationships.

