## Real-Time Sync

### See Changes Immediately

Belcoda uses Rocicorp Zero for real-time database synchronization. When someone signs up for an event, their profile updates immediately in your open browser tab. When a colleague adds a tag, you see it without refreshing. When activity happens, the timeline extends automatically.

This real-time sync eliminates the coordination overhead of "did you refresh?" conversations. Multiple organizers can work simultaneously without stepping on each other's changes. The system handles conflict resolution automatically, prioritizing the most recent write.

Debounced updates prevent excessive re-rendering. Search inputs wait 200 milliseconds after your last keystroke before querying. Form auto-saves wait 300 milliseconds after your last edit. These small delays create fluidity without lag.

---

## Data Quality

### Prevent Duplicates

The system searches for existing records during event signups and imports. Match by email first, then phone number. If a match exists, update the existing profile rather than creating a duplicate. This matching happens automatically, reducing manual de-duplication work.

### Verification Status

Track which contact methods are actually valid. Email verification happens through confirmation links. Phone verification happens through WhatsApp handshake. The system marks verification status clearly on profiles, so you know which channels are reliable.

Unverified contacts aren't blocked—people can still be in your database with unverified information—but the status helps you prioritize reliable channels for important communications.

### Soft Deletes

Records are never truly deleted from the database. Instead, they're marked with a `deletedAt` timestamp and filtered from queries. This soft delete pattern preserves audit trails and allows recovery if someone was deleted by mistake.

Deleted records don't appear in standard views or exports, but administrators can access them if needed. The system tracks who deleted records and when, providing accountability.

